elements.2211.03055_37cf057eab28f37eec8f8fb0a94b7: With the development of depth sensors in recent years, RGBD object tracking has received significant attention
elements.2211.03055_4e4f52ad5d4e81eeb9234935c19f8: Compared with the traditional RGB object tracking, the addition of the depth modality can effectively solve the target and background interference
elements.2211.03055_6b1876645cb347402ad10fd1b3bcc: However, some existing RGBD trackers use the two modalities separately and thus some particularly useful shared information between them is ignored
elements.2211.03055_fddea4670acbdafde476fac168460: On the other hand, some methods attempt to fuse the two modalities by treating them equally, resulting in the missing of modality-specific features.
elements.2211.03055_377991f6936bc4c0172dbb6fa4f3a: To tackle these limitations, we propose a novel Dual-fused Modality-aware Tracker (termed DMTracker) which aims to learn informative and discriminative representations of the target objects for robust RGBD tracking
elements.2211.03055_53dec87f23b4a9d928b014ed882fb: The first fusion module focuses on extracting the shared information between modalities based on cross-modal attention
elements.2211.03055_6f98bc9af7004f6fa26452e6f1f34: The second aims at integrating the RGB-specific and depth-specific information to enhance the fused features
elements.2211.03055_3ece33c09b7af858c912772b572b1: By fusing both the modality-shared and modality-specific information in a modality-aware scheme, our DMTracker can learn discriminative representations in complex tracking scenes.
elements.2211.03055_e6991db9d5ce1f7936422d4d8b99a: Experiments show that our proposed tracker achieves very promising results on challenging RGBD benchmarks.
elements.2211.03055_6daabd6ddee581ac0530688d70f2b: Object tracking is to localize an arbitrary object in a video sequence, given only the object description in the first frame
elements.2211.03055_4298164790498adf36fa51ef18ec9: It can be applied in lots of applications in video surveillance, autonomous driving
elements.2211.03055_250d5150e706bd7c3dba69062cfb7: Recent years witness the development of RGBD (RGB+Depth) object tracking thanks to the affordable and accurate depth cameras
elements.2211.03055_18614fda278373602868793443674: RGBD tracking aims to track the objects more robustly and accurately with the help of depth information, even in color-failed scenarios,
elements.2211.03055_2e49348a4ec9154add24211f6dc6a: Compared to conventional RGB-based tracking, the major difficulty of RGBD tracking is the modality discrepancy resulting from intrinsically distinct information obtained from different modalities
elements.2211.03055_28e0d98b143445a9c2a2bc37b55d8: For accurate and robust tracking, existing RGBD trackers have many attempts on either RGB and depth fusion
elements.2211.03055_591bd879a45c5e5e4647918abc51f: , or RGB and depth feature extraction
elements.2211.03055_4c30e5c20c48732c49a50fb0b659b: For example, early RGBD trackers fuse RGB and depth HoG features by using different weights
elements.2211.03055_5182f87b188e8cc3e60c76f734727: applied the Kernel Correlation Filter (KCF) in RGB and depth maps, respectively.
elements.2211.03055_05e271e96b426518a4bbf2821c9d5: With the boosting of deep learning, researchers combine depth information with pre-trained RGB trackers to improve tracking performance
elements.2211.03055_feef4e43dc755a085a8d7d1dd7eb0: utilizes depth information to enhance RGB features via depth-aware convolutions.
elements.2211.03055_cd5d5afe2f88229f7bc847c83c2c9: , which utilized the depth colormaps for feature extraction and fused color and depth features via a simple operation like element-wise maximum.
elements.2211.03055_56ebd1288875a3278e4e10127e486: However, on the one hand, a simple modality fusion strategy generally treats the two modalities equally
elements.2211.03055_dfde24e59322e4155262183b5091a: Thus, some modality-specific features which are strongly complementary cannot be discovered
elements.2211.03055_2314765f36002be18291a14ed24c6: For example, such fusing operations have side effects on the color modality
elements.2211.03055_75e58ffd39cef033c48770f22574b: As RGB frames are informative, preserving the color and texture information is important for tracking.
elements.2211.03055_25aeada803c643f76070f87004f4a: On the other hand, separately using RGB and depth information may lose the shared information between different modalities
elements.2211.03055_2998fb171cb6ddfcb9b5f9baf2000: Thus, with simply-fused features only, or using color and depth features separately, the upper bound of the discrimination ability of the feature representation is limited
elements.2211.03055_0e0f52c4e813289a018bed9d77179: Up to now, few methods explicitly exploit both intra- and inter-modality characteristics for RGBD tracking
elements.2211.03055_2e93f7187bf211793cf92b2826a2d: Such deficiencies impede the tracking performance, and thus designing a high-performance RGBD tracker is still challenging.
elements.2211.03055_8df74eaf8f1a7470e11a15b7d15fe: Existing works in multi-modal learning demonstrate that models can benefit from exploring both the shared information and modality-specific characteristics
elements.2211.03055_7fcc5427a2bb3768dbf815fbc0bd8: Inspired by this, in this paper, we aim to tackle the above deficiencies by proposing
elements.2211.03055_6534d77670851f230f073a9be8eb1: The proposed framework consists of dual fusions, which apply the modality similarity and discrepancy for a robust feature representation
elements.2211.03055_011f09dcbc9dd73d9aba5ac0ef094: The first fusion module is the Cross-Modal Integration Module (CMIM), which is based on cross-attention
elements.2211.03055_02478baf7ddb772ef7304657f9934: The second fusion module is Specificity Preserving Module (SPM)
elements.2211.03055_d6892d3713736a840ca7c2061584d: Specifically, CMIM explores the affinities between RGB and depth features to obtain shared information between different modalities
elements.2211.03055_0a59311e42bc99168c3adbca00f41: The obtained modality-shared features represent the correlation between RGB and depth channels through cross-modal attention
elements.2211.03055_b508b3c5574ee5ca6e2164f31d429: SPM compensate the modality-shared features by fusing the weighted modality-specific features and the shared ones
elements.2211.03055_f8c41694b225a8f1a4b078da099a4: Thus, the second fusion tries to make up the missing specific information from the individual modalities
elements.2211.03055_cf327d3a25591f1810764c5606579: In DMTracker, intra-modality and inter-modality characteristics are both preserved through modality-aware fusions for similarity matching between tracking templates and search regions
elements.2211.03055_e7c53285ca3ab68314bc7ba85c4b2: This scheme can compensate for the lack of modality-specific information and enhance the modality-shared features, which finally improves the overall representation ability.
elements.2211.03055_71e4bf1804da2f46ed04a1df1354e: Experiments on popular RGBD tracking benchmarks demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed method.
elements.2211.03055_4d9c9b943a1e110f78fc309d73937: We propose a new tracking method dedicated to RGBD object tracking
elements.2211.03055_ef7252da14fbd3364d0ea5ea667c4: It is capable of end-to-end offline training and real-time applications.
elements.2211.03055_e98c3cad7e0e56e15015a8e0221fd: We develop two novel modality-aware fusion modules that incorporate both modality-shared and modality-specific information for robust tracking.
elements.2211.03055_d7fbeeee5c40963f688c3e87cd65c: The proposed DMTracker achieves state-of-the-art performance on existing challenging RGBD tracking benchmarks with running at real-time speed.

elements.2211.03055_e5c4f82028b4b0baae002bcb51835: Furthermore, we carry out an attribute-based evaluation to study the performance under different challenges.

elements.2211.03055_0f3604fd63425fe82a2269d8f7f83: Since the proposed DMTracker is used to fuse cross-modal features and learn a unified representation, we ablate each key component for analysis.
elements.2211.03055_d991beea8d0f342a63385655d0d7f: The base model is constructed by removing the whole dual-fused modality-aware network
elements.2211.03055_1f569966087fd37a3beef412c3c0d: The fused features are obtained by simply obtaining the element-wise addition of RGB and depth feature maps
elements.2211.03055_f5c96cf50c450d66862e06bb88071: , the tracking performance first degrades with only CMIM or SPM and then highly improves with adding the CMIM and SPM
elements.2211.03055_1575418952c998240998cdaa85772: , the CMIM will bring very informative and even redundant features which leads to the sub-optimal performance
elements.2211.03055_d4176eab9dbdc82e06259b22facfc: With only SPM, the interaction of cross-modal information is lacking, so the model does not fully exploit the modality-aware correlation information
elements.2211.03055_2a5887d081521bf7f0277668d4d22: Then, by adding the CMIM and SPM, the redundant information is effectively suppressed, shared and specificity information is enhanced and thus the tracking performance improves.
elements.2211.03055_27cb68d310e803097ea9846c67f2b: Effects on modalities fusion order in SPM.
elements.2211.03055_2efdc27dd3affad6a9f5cabead480: In the specificity preserving module (SPM) of our DMTracker, We first add depth-specific features to RGBD features and then fuse them with weighted RGB-specific features
elements.2211.03055_2129c767e63af52728338dcdc80b1: When given different orders of specific modalities, the performance of the tracker degrades.
elements.2211.03055_445cc33f311d980b1c7cee6cc7229: This can be explained by the fact that the RGB features are more informative than depth features, and this part of the information is dominant in the tracking process
elements.2211.03055_d149b91ad0783d8e9f3622f237a65: Assume the spatial information is added in high weight at the end fusion
elements.2211.03055_70427d92cf19ca77ac8d759c92ef4: In that case, the proportion of visual information in the fusion feature is weakened
elements.2211.03055_a00b880d07b7f0bea2c540064320e: Mixing excess spatial information confuses the tracker.
elements.2211.03055_6d7a2ba58c37f429d8e92f4446826: In this paper, we proposed a novel DMTracker to learn dual-fused modality-aware representations for RGBD tracking
elements.2211.03055_62961b1211f1f7395fd9375e1d9a1: On the one hand, the proposed cross-modal integration module can learn the shared information between RGB and depth channels through cross-modal attention
elements.2211.03055_dfb40cffcb50e4e0ff9ecf5e64340: On the other hand, the following specificity preserving module can adaptively fuse the shared features and RGB and depth features to get discriminative representations
elements.2211.03055_37c05d2296944dae5437d17385674: Extensive experiments validate the superior performance of the proposed DMTracker, as well as the effectiveness of each component.
